-- ============================================================
-- THE BOOK OF MORMON
-- ============================================================
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The FOH sound console is a DiGiCo SD7T configured for 132 input channels', 'technical', 'fact', 'Massive channel count for a comedy musical'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The main speaker system uses L-Acoustics dV-DOSC compact line arrays hung nearly horizontally in front of the proscenium', 'technical', 'fact', 'Unusual horizontal orientation for a Broadway house'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'For tap-dancing scenes, wireless microphones are sewn into performers'' pants with the element pointed at their shoes instead of using separate foot mics', 'technical', 'fact', 'A creative miking solution unique to this production'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The lighting rig uses 250 conventional lamps and 60 moving lights controlled by two consoles: a grandMA for movers and an ETC Ion for conventionals', 'technical', 'fact', 'Brian MacDevitt described it as lean and mean by Broadway spectacle standards'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'During the nightmare sequence, a painted scenic drop is sucked into the floor through a stage trap in two seconds flat', 'backstage', 'fact', 'Scott Pask called it a feat of stagecraft and technical expertise'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Martin MAC moving lights project the leaping flames effect during the nightmare number, chosen because they were the only movers that could do realistic fire projection', 'technical', 'fact', 'Brian MacDevitt spent more time lighting this number than any other in the show'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The pit musicians use a dozen Aviom A-16II personal monitor mixers fed through eight Aphex 1788A mic preamps', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Allows each musician to control their own monitor mix'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Sound effects play from QLab on redundant Mac Minis with MOTU 828 audio interfaces', 'technical', 'fact', 'Dual-computer redundancy ensures no missed cues'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Props for the village pageant include bonnets made from cereal boxes, license plates, and soda bottles', 'design', 'fact', 'Designed to look handmade by the characters themselves'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Hair designer Josh Marquette created wigs for the pageant sequence made from actual leaves and twigs', 'design', 'fact', 'Reinforces the DIY aesthetic of the villagers'' show-within-a-show'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Costume designer Ann Roth fitted a character''s cape with LED lights, inspired by what she called a Cheryl Tiegs in the eighties look', 'design', 'fact', 'A deliberate camp aesthetic choice from a legendary designer'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original leads were double-miked with both DPA 4061 miniatures and Sennheiser MKE lavs paired with SK-5212 wireless transmitters for redundancy', 'technical', 'fact', 'Ensures no audio dropout on the principal performers'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Won 9 of its 14 Tony nominations in 2011, including Best Musical, Best Book, Best Score, Best Direction, and Best Orchestrations', 'award', 'fact', 'One of the most-nominated and most-awarded shows of its era'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Recouped its entire $11.4 million investment in just nine months', 'numbers', 'fact', 'Fueled by dynamic pricing with premium seats reaching $477'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Has surpassed 5,500 performances at the Eugene O''Neill Theatre, making it the venue''s longest-running show in history', 'numbers', 'fact', 'Broke the house box-office record more than 50 times'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Skipped an out-of-town tryout and went directly to Broadway, a bold gamble by producers Scott Rudin and Anne Garefino', 'production', 'fact', 'Went through a half-dozen workshops over four years instead'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Trey Parker and Matt Stone first met Robert Lopez after attending Avenue Q on Broadway in 2003, when Lopez and Jeff Marx spotted them in the audience', 'history', 'fact', 'The chance encounter backstage led to a decade-long collaboration'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Cheyenne Jackson starred in the earliest developmental workshops in 2008 before the role was recast', 'cast', 'fact', 'The show went through extensive casting changes during development'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Ben Platt played Elder Cunningham on Broadway from January 2014 to January 2015, two years before originating the title role in Dear Evan Hansen', 'cast', 'fact', 'The role was a stepping stone to his Tony-winning breakthrough'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original cast recording won the 2012 Grammy Award for Best Musical Theater Album', 'award', 'fact', 'Beat recordings from revivals of Anything Goes and How to Succeed'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Josh Gad originated the role of Elder Cunningham and Andrew Rannells originated Elder Price, both earning Tony nominations', 'cast', 'fact', 'Both actors went on to major film and television careers'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Nikki M. James won the Tony for Best Featured Actress in a Musical for originating the role of Nabulungi', 'award', 'fact', 'One of the show''s nine Tony wins in 2011'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Orchestrations by Larry Hochman and Stephen Oremus won the Tony for Best Orchestrations', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Oremus also served as musical director and vocal arranger'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Lifetime gross has exceeded $800 million across all productions worldwide', 'numbers', 'fact', 'Includes Broadway, multiple tours, and international companies'),
('The Book of Mormon', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Celebrating its 15th anniversary on Broadway in 2026 with $15 digital lottery tickets and a special performance on March 19', 'culture', 'fact', 'Now the tenth longest-running show in Broadway history'),

-- ============================================================
-- SPRING AWAKENING
-- ============================================================
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Lighting designer Kevin Adams used a dual lighting language: brilliant white for 19th-century dialogue and heavily saturated color from neon tubes for musical numbers', 'technical', 'fact', 'The visual shift was the audience''s cue for when characters broke into their inner voices'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Adams bracketed tubes of primary-color neon light to the theater walls, shooting from the stage outward into the audience like a starburst', 'technical', 'fact', 'Broke the proscenium boundary to create an immersive concert-like feel'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Dozens of bare blue lightbulbs slowly descended from above the stage during key scenes, creating one of the show''s most iconic visual images', 'technical', 'fact', 'A simple but unforgettable lighting effect'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Actors in 19th-century costumes pulled out handheld microphones when they began to sing, making the mics a visual shorthand for inner voice breaking free from repression', 'backstage', 'fact', 'A signature staging concept that defined the show''s identity'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The set was deliberately minimal: a bare stage with wooden chairs that the cast rearranged between scenes, treating the performers as both characters and stagehands', 'design', 'fact', 'Christine Jones'' set design rejected Broadway spectacle for raw simplicity'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'An 8-piece rock band performed on stage behind the actors rather than in a traditional pit, visible to the audience throughout the entire show', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Duncan Sheik wanted the band to feel like part of the world, not hidden support'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The onstage band included guitars, bass, cello, keyboards, drums, and violin, blending rock instrumentation with classical strings', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The cello and violin gave the rock score an aching, acoustic quality'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Bill T. Jones choreographed the show despite having no prior Broadway musical experience, bringing modern dance vocabulary to the staging', 'production', 'fact', 'Jones is primarily known as a contemporary dance choreographer and MacArthur Fellow'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Won 8 Tony Awards in 2007 including Best Musical, beating rival nominees Curtains, Grey Gardens, and Mary Poppins', 'award', 'fact', 'A downtown show triumphing over bigger-budget competitors'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Duncan Sheik and Steven Sater won the Tony for Best Original Score, making Sheik the first primarily rock/pop artist to win the award', 'award', 'fact', 'Sheik was best known for his 1996 hit single Barely Breathing'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The cast recording was recorded on October 5-6, 2006, before the show even officially opened on Broadway on December 10', 'production', 'fact', 'An unusual move that helped build buzz during the preview period'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jonathan Groff was 21 years old when he originated the role of Melchior, his Broadway debut', 'cast', 'fact', 'He went on to star in Hamilton, Frozen, and Mindhunter'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Lea Michele was 20 when she originated the role of Wendla, also her Broadway debut, after performing in the show''s development since age 14', 'cast', 'fact', 'She had been with the project through six years of workshops'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'John Gallagher Jr. won the Tony for Best Featured Actor at age 22 for originating the role of Moritz', 'award', 'fact', 'His acceptance speech became a viral moment'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show ran for 859 performances at the Eugene O''Neill Theatre from December 2006 to January 2009', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A strong run for a show with no star names at opening'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Developed at the Atlantic Theater Company off-Broadway starting in May 2006 before transferring to Broadway seven months later', 'history', 'fact', 'The off-Broadway run sold out its entire engagement'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Based on Frank Wedekind''s 1891 play of the same name, which was banned in Germany for its depictions of adolescent sexuality and was not performed until 1906', 'history', 'fact', 'The source material was considered scandalous for over a century'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Tom Hulce, who played Amadeus in the 1984 film, served as one of the show''s lead producers', 'production', 'fact', 'An Oscar-nominated actor turned Broadway producer'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Audience members seated on stage in bleachers flanked the performers during musical numbers, sometimes being sung directly to', 'backstage', 'fact', 'Around 30 audience members per show sat on stage alongside the cast'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Deaf West Theatre produced a bilingual ASL/English revival in 2015 that used deaf and hearing actors performing simultaneously', 'history', 'fact', 'The revival was nominated for 3 Tony Awards including Best Revival'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Costume designer Susan Hilferty dressed the cast in a mix of 1890s period clothing and modern touches like Converse sneakers', 'design', 'fact', 'The anachronistic costume choices reinforced the show''s dual timeline'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Michael Mayer directed the show with a concept that treated each song as a private concert where characters express what they cannot say aloud in the period setting', 'production', 'fact', 'The concert-within-a-play format was the show''s central innovation'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Kevin Adams won his first of four career Tony Awards for Best Lighting Design for this production', 'award', 'fact', 'The lighting was considered as revolutionary as the staging itself'),
('Spring Awakening', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show grossed over $77 million during its Broadway run on a modest production budget', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A financially successful run for a show with minimal scenery'),

-- ============================================================
-- WEST SIDE STORY
-- ============================================================
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show was originally conceived in 1949 as East Side Story, about conflict between a Catholic family and a Jewish family during the Easter-Passover season on the Lower East Side', 'history', 'fact', 'Jerome Robbins, Leonard Bernstein, and Arthur Laurents shelved the idea for six years'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Stephen Sondheim was 27 years old and did not want to be only a lyricist, but his mentor Oscar Hammerstein II convinced him that he would benefit from the experience', 'history', 'fact', 'It became Sondheim''s Broadway debut and launched his career'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Bernstein initially shared co-lyricist credit with Sondheim but magnanimously dropped his name from the lyricist credit before opening night', 'history', 'fact', 'Bernstein recognized Sondheim''s contributions deserved sole credit'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jerome Robbins negotiated eight weeks of rehearsal time, double the standard four weeks for a Broadway show at the time', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The extended rehearsal period was unprecedented and essential for the complex choreography'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Robbins kept the actors playing Jets and Sharks completely separated during rehearsals, forbidding them from socializing, eating together, or even being friendly offstage', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The enforced hostility created real tension that transferred to the stage'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Oliver Smith''s original set used a series of sliding panels and projected backgrounds rather than traditional box sets, allowing scenes to flow cinematically without blackouts', 'design', 'fact', 'The fluid scenic transitions were revolutionary for 1957 Broadway staging'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Irene Sharaff color-coded the costumes: Jets wore cool colors like blues and yellows while Sharks wore warm reds, purples, and blacks', 'design', 'fact', 'The audience could identify gang allegiance at a glance from any seat in the house'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original orchestration by Sid Ramin and Irwin Kostal called for a 30-piece orchestra, unusually large for the era', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Bernstein''s complex score required near-symphonic forces in the pit'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Neither of the original leads, Larry Kert and Carol Lawrence, were well known before the show, which was considered a risk by producers', 'cast', 'fact', 'Both became stars because of the production'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Chita Rivera originated the role of Anita at age 24, performing Robbins'' athletic choreography eight shows a week', 'cast', 'fact', 'The role launched one of the longest careers in Broadway history'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production opened at the Winter Garden Theatre on September 26, 1957, and ran for 732 performances', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A respectable run that grew legendary through the 1961 film'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Won only 2 Tony Awards in 1958, losing Best Musical to The Music Man, in what is now considered one of the biggest Tony upsets in history', 'award', 'fact', 'The show won for choreography and scenic design but not the top prize'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2009 revival at the Palace Theatre featured new Spanish-language translations of several songs by Lin-Manuel Miranda', 'history', 'fact', 'Miranda was 28 and had just opened In the Heights when he took on the project'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'In the 2009 revival, the Shark women sang portions of songs including A Boy Like That entirely in Spanish, a first for a major Broadway revival', 'production', 'fact', 'The bilingual approach was both praised for authenticity and debated for accessibility'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The prologue features nearly ten minutes of continuous dance with almost no dialogue, establishing the entire world of the show through movement alone', 'backstage', 'fact', 'Robbins insisted the choreography tell the story before a word is spoken'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Bernstein''s score uses tritones — intervals of three whole tones — as a recurring motif, an interval historically called the devil''s interval for its dissonant quality', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The tritone appears in Cool, Maria, and throughout the orchestration'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The finger-snapping that opens the show was Robbins'' idea, created to build tension from silence into the explosive choreography that follows', 'backstage', 'fact', 'One of the most iconic opening moments in Broadway history'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Betty Comden and Adolph Green were originally asked to write the lyrics but chose to work on Peter Pan instead, leading to Sondheim getting the job', 'history', 'fact', 'A fateful scheduling conflict that changed Broadway history'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The dance at the gym sequence required actors to perform Jerome Robbins'' choreography while simultaneously establishing romantic chemistry across gang lines in real time', 'backstage', 'fact', 'Robbins rehearsed the gym sequence separately for weeks before integrating it'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production tried out at the National Theatre in Washington, D.C., before opening on Broadway', 'production', 'fact', 'The D.C. tryout led to significant restructuring of the second act'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Bernstein composed the balcony scene music, Tonight, in a single afternoon after weeks of struggling with it', 'song', 'fact', 'One of the most famous melodies in the American songbook came together in hours'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2020 revival, directed by Ivo van Hove, used live video feeds and cameras on stage, with no traditional scenery, before closing due to the pandemic after just 24 performances', 'production', 'fact', 'A radical reimagining that barely got to be seen'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The concert suite from the score has been performed by virtually every major symphony orchestra in the world, making it one of the most-programmed Broadway works in classical music', 'culture', 'fact', 'Bernstein''s score bridges Broadway and the concert hall like no other'),
('West Side Story', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Arthur Laurents'' original stage direction notes specified that the rumble should be almost balletic, with the violence stylized through dance rather than realistic fighting', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The rumble is choreographed combat, not stage combat in the traditional sense'),

-- ============================================================
-- MOULIN ROUGE! THE MUSICAL
-- ============================================================
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The lighting rig includes approximately 200 moving heads plus thousands of individual lightbulbs throughout the theater, totaling over 25 tons of lighting fixtures', 'technical', 'fact', 'PRG supplied the massive rig that transforms the entire theater into the club'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Programmer Brad Gray ran an ETC Eos Ti console controlling 6,000 channels across 10 interconnected magic sheets', 'technical', 'fact', 'The lighting system syncs to SMPTE timecode from the musical director''s Ableton computer'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Sound designer Peter Hylenski concealed roughly 200 speakers in and around the set because the scenic design breaking through the proscenium made typical speaker positions unusable', 'technical', 'fact', 'The first Broadway installation of the Meyer Sound UPQ-D3 ultra-wide-coverage speaker'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The core sound system uses close to 130 Meyer Sound loudspeakers, with cast members wearing Sennheiser MKE1 elements on custom headsets via Lectrosonics SSM wireless packs', 'technical', 'fact', 'An unusually large speaker count hidden within an immersive scenic environment'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'A 30-foot by 14-foot rotating platform built by PRG holds the dressing room set piece, with all scenic drops and the front-of-house elephant controlled by the Stage Command automation system', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The automation is invisible but drives the show''s most spectacular scenic transitions'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The front-of-house elephant stands about 18 feet tall on a balcony on house right, painted blue with what the designer described as wonderfully sad eyes', 'design', 'fact', 'Inspired by the spectacular elephant in the garden of the real Moulin Rouge in Paris'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Nine different types of red fabric were sourced because there was not enough of any single red to cover the entire theater transformation', 'design', 'fact', 'The variety of reds creates visual depth rather than flatness across the enormous scenic area'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Scenic designer Derek McLane extended the set design beyond the stage and into the audience, decorating the Al Hirschfeld Theatre lobby and auditorium to look like the Moulin Rouge nightclub', 'design', 'fact', 'The immersive environment begins the moment you enter the theater'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Aaron Tveit won the Tony for Best Leading Actor in a Musical as the sole nominee in his category, making him the first to win by default since the category''s creation', 'award', 'fact', 'A unique outcome caused by the compressed 2020 season that nominated fewer shows'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Won 10 Tony Awards at the 2021 ceremony, including Best Musical, the most wins of any show that season', 'award', 'fact', 'The ceremony was delayed a year due to the pandemic and held at the Winter Garden Theatre'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The jukebox score incorporates over 70 songs from artists spanning decades, from Jacques Offenbach to Beyonce, arranged and mashed up by Justin Levine', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Song selections changed during the Boston tryout and continue to be updated for cultural relevance'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Choreographer Sonya Tayeh won the Tony for Best Choreography, her first Broadway show', 'award', 'fact', 'Tayeh was previously known for work on So You Think You Can Dance'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Boston tryout at the Emerson Colonial Theatre ran from June to August 2018, more than a year before the Broadway opening', 'production', 'fact', 'An extended pre-Broadway engagement that allowed significant reworking'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Opened on Broadway at the Al Hirschfeld Theatre on July 25, 2019, after previews beginning June 28', 'production', 'fact', 'One of the last major musicals to open before the pandemic shutdown'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Karen Olivo originated the role of Satine on Broadway but did not return when the show reopened after the pandemic shutdown, citing industry concerns', 'cast', 'fact', 'Her departure made headlines and sparked conversation about working conditions on Broadway'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Director Alex Timbers staged the show to feel like a rock concert inside a nightclub, with the audience treated as patrons of the Moulin Rouge', 'production', 'fact', 'The fourth wall is deliberately broken throughout the production'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Catherine Zuber designed over 100 costumes for the production, many featuring corsets, bustles, and hand-beaded details', 'design', 'fact', 'Tony-winning costume design that references both 1899 Paris and modern fashion'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The neon Moulin Rouge sign above the stage is built to scale and pulses with the show''s lighting throughout each performance', 'design', 'fact', 'One of the largest practical neon installations on a Broadway stage'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The production has grossed over $300 million lifetime on Broadway', 'numbers', 'fact', 'Consistently among the top-grossing shows on Broadway each week'),
('Moulin Rouge! The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Cast members perform medleys where songs shift every 30 to 60 seconds, requiring rapid vocal style changes from pop to rock to R&B to Broadway belting', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The vocal demands are among the most diverse on Broadway'),

-- ============================================================
-- CABARET
-- ============================================================
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Boris Aronson''s original 1966 set was dominated by an enormous trapezoidal mirror made from lightweight mylar that could tilt to reflect distorted images of performers or the actual audience back at themselves', 'design', 'fact', 'Reinforced the show''s central message: it could happen here'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 1966 original had no overture and no show curtain — the audience entered to a bare stage with only the massive tilting mirror visible', 'backstage', 'fact', 'A radical departure from standard Broadway presentation at the time'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production won 8 Tony Awards in 1967 including Best Musical, Best Direction for Harold Prince, and Best Scenic Design for Boris Aronson', 'award', 'fact', 'Among the most decorated musicals of the 1960s'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Joel Grey originated the role of the Emcee in 1966 and returned to play the role again in the 1987 revival, more than 20 years later', 'cast', 'fact', 'One of the rare instances of an actor reprising a signature role decades later on Broadway'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 1998 revival transformed Studio 54 into the Kit Kat Klub, with cabaret tables on stage, audience members seated among the performers, and the traditional theater seating used as a backdrop', 'design', 'fact', 'Sam Mendes and Rob Marshall turned the actual nightclub into the fictional one'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Studio 54 was a working nightclub and concert venue that had to be converted into a functioning Broadway theater for the 1998 revival, with the Roundabout Theatre Company adding stage rigging and theater infrastructure', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The venue had never hosted a traditional Broadway production before'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Kit Kat Band performed on stage in character throughout the entire 1998 revival, never hidden in a pit, wearing costumes and interacting with the Emcee', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The visible band reinforced the nightclub atmosphere and blurred the line between show and reality'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Alan Cumming originated the Emcee in the 1998 revival, performing with a physicality and androgynous sexuality that redefined the character from Joel Grey''s more impish original interpretation', 'cast', 'fact', 'Cumming won the Tony for Best Leading Actor and became synonymous with the role'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Natasha Richardson won the Tony for Best Leading Actress as Sally Bowles in the 1998 revival, beating three other nominees', 'award', 'fact', 'Her performance was considered a career-defining turn'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 1998 revival ran for 2,377 performances over six years at Studio 54, making it the longest-running revival in Broadway history at that time', 'numbers', 'fact', 'Far exceeding the original production''s run of 1,166 performances'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 1998 revival won 4 Tony Awards including Best Revival, Best Leading Actor, Best Leading Actress, and Best Featured Actor for Ron Rifkin', 'award', 'fact', 'A sweep of the major performance categories'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original 1966 production opened at the Broadhurst Theatre, then transferred to the Imperial and finally the Broadway Theatre before closing in 1969 after 1,166 performances', 'numbers', 'fact', 'An unusual triple-venue run reflecting strong audience demand'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Aronson created a stylized black limbo space for the original rather than realistic sets, with smaller pieces rolled in on wagons and depth provided by streetlights, storefronts, and a cursive red neon Cabaret sign', 'design', 'fact', 'The abstract void was revolutionary for a Broadway musical in 1966'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2024 revival at the August Wilson Theatre starred Eddie Redmayne as the Emcee, with a production that further stripped the staging to its darkest, most political core', 'production', 'fact', 'The third major Broadway production of the show in under 60 years'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The score by John Kander and Fred Ebb was their first major Broadway success, launching a partnership that would span decades and produce Chicago, Kiss of the Spider Woman, and more', 'history', 'fact', 'The team defined a darker, more cynical strain of the Broadway musical'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The musical is based on Christopher Isherwood''s 1939 novel Goodbye to Berlin and John Van Druten''s 1951 play I Am a Camera, set in Weimar Republic Berlin as the Nazis rise to power', 'history', 'fact', 'Isherwood lived in Berlin from 1929 to 1933 and drew from personal experience'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Harold Prince directed the original with a Brechtian concept, using the Emcee and Kit Kat Klub as a lens through which all the dramatic action was filtered and commented upon', 'production', 'fact', 'Prince brought the distancing techniques of Brecht to mainstream Broadway'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jean Rosenthal designed the lighting for the original 1966 production, one of the last major Broadway shows she lit before her death in 1969', 'technical', 'fact', 'Rosenthal is considered the mother of modern theatrical lighting design'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Patricia Zipprodt won the Tony for Best Costume Design for the original, creating distinct visual worlds for the Kit Kat performers and the everyday Berlin characters', 'design', 'fact', 'The costume contrast between the club and the streets reinforced the show''s dual reality'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Emcee''s final costume reveal in the 1998 revival included a concentration camp uniform under his nightclub outfit, a devastating visual that was not in the original production', 'design', 'fact', 'Sam Mendes added the image to make the political stakes visceral'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Multiple major film and TV stars have played Sally Bowles on Broadway including Brooke Shields, Molly Ringwald, and Emma Stone, each bringing the role to new audiences', 'cast', 'fact', 'The role has become a magnet for crossover casting'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Ron Field choreographed the original 1966 production, winning the Tony for Best Choreography for the Kit Kat Klub numbers', 'production', 'fact', 'His choreography established the seductive, Weimar-era movement vocabulary that all revivals have built upon'),
('Cabaret', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Rob Marshall co-directed and choreographed the 1998 revival before going on to direct the 2002 film of Chicago', 'production', 'fact', 'His Cabaret staging was a proving ground for the cinematic musical approach he later brought to film'),

-- ============================================================
-- FIDDLER ON THE ROOF
-- ============================================================
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show was originally going to musicalize Sholem Aleichem''s novel Wandering Stars about a traveling Yiddish theater troupe, but the writers abandoned it because it required roughly 40 minor characters', 'history', 'fact', 'They pivoted to the Tevye stories instead, a decision that created a masterpiece'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Boris Aronson''s set design was inspired by Marc Chagall''s painting The Fiddler, also known as Green Violinist, depicting a fiddler perched above a village', 'design', 'fact', 'The title and the visual world both came from Chagall'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Before settling on the final title, the show went through working titles including The Old Country, Tevye, Not So Long Ago, Not So Far Away, and Where Poppa Came From', 'history', 'fact', 'A long search for the perfect name'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Bock and Harnick began writing the show on September 11, 1961, which happened to be Rosh Hashanah, the Jewish New Year', 'history', 'fact', 'An auspicious coincidence for a show about Jewish tradition'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Stephen Sondheim urged Jerome Robbins to direct the show after hearing the score at a private party at librettist Joseph Stein''s home in New Rochelle', 'history', 'fact', 'Sondheim''s recommendation brought Robbins to the project'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jerome Robbins developed the concept of Tradition as the opening number during rehearsals, insisting the show needed to establish the entire social fabric of the village before the story could begin', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The opening number was not in the original script and became the show''s thesis statement'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Robbins rehearsed the company for weeks doing improvisation exercises about Jewish shtetl life before allowing them to touch the actual script or score', 'backstage', 'fact', 'Actors researched occupations, family relationships, and daily routines of their characters'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The famous bottle dance at the wedding uses bottles that are attached to the performers'' hats with a combination of Velcro and small platforms, though the actual balancing still requires extraordinary skill', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The bottles are secured but the dancing is entirely real and athletically demanding'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original orchestration by Don Walker featured a 26-piece orchestra with prominent use of clarinet, violin, and accordion to evoke klezmer music', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The blend of Broadway and Eastern European folk instrumentation defined the show''s sound'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Won 9 Tony Awards in 1965 including Best Musical, Best Director, Best Choreography, Best Actor for Zero Mostel, and Best Score for Bock and Harnick', 'award', 'fact', 'A dominant sweep of the major categories'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production ran for 3,242 performances at the Imperial Theatre, becoming the longest-running musical in Broadway history until it was surpassed by Grease in 1980', 'numbers', 'fact', 'Held the record for 8 years'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Zero Mostel originated the role of Tevye but left the show after only nine months due to contract disputes, and was replaced by Luther Adler', 'cast', 'fact', 'Despite his short run, Mostel''s Tevye became the definitive interpretation'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The role of Tevye has been played on Broadway by Zero Mostel, Herschel Bernardi, Theodore Bikel, Harvey Fierstein, Danny Burstein, and Alfred Molina, among others', 'cast', 'fact', 'One of the most coveted roles in the Broadway canon'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Aronson''s set featured a series of periaktoi — revolving three-sided scenic units — that could spin to reveal different locations in the village without full scene changes', 'design', 'fact', 'An elegant mechanical solution for fluid storytelling'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show opened on September 22, 1964, at the Imperial Theatre, produced by Harold Prince', 'production', 'fact', 'Prince produced but did not direct, leaving that to Robbins'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Patricia Zipprodt designed the costumes for the original, creating distinct silhouettes for each family in Anatevka with historically accurate fabrics', 'design', 'fact', 'Zipprodt researched actual shtetl clothing from museum collections'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show tried out at the Fisher Theatre in Detroit before its Broadway opening, where it ran over three hours and required significant cuts', 'production', 'fact', 'The Detroit tryout trimmed nearly 40 minutes from the running time'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'A Yiddish-language production directed by Joel Grey ran off-Broadway in 2018 at the Museum of Jewish Heritage and became a surprise hit, later transferring to Stage 42', 'culture', 'fact', 'Performed entirely in Yiddish with English and Russian supertitles'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The dream sequence featuring Fruma-Sarah required the actress to be elevated on a hidden platform and tower above the other performers in flowing white robes', 'backstage', 'fact', 'One of the most technically demanding moments in the show, staged differently in every production'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Robbins'' choreography for the wedding scene built from individual folk dance steps into a full-company celebration that takes over the entire stage', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The escalating energy of the hora was carefully choreographed to feel spontaneous'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2015 revival directed by Bartlett Sher at the Broadway Theatre featured a revolving stage and was nominated for 3 Tony Awards', 'production', 'fact', 'Danny Burstein was nominated for Best Leading Actor as Tevye'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Has been produced in over 40 countries and translated into more than 20 languages, making it one of the most-performed musicals worldwide', 'culture', 'fact', 'Its themes of tradition and displacement resonate across cultures'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production''s fiddler was a violinist perched on a small platform above the stage, playing live throughout the performance', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The visible fiddler became the show''s visual signature'),
('Fiddler on the Roof', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jean Rosenthal designed the lighting for the original production, using warm amber washes to evoke the golden light of memory and nostalgia', 'technical', 'fact', 'Rosenthal''s lighting gave the show its signature warmth'),

-- ============================================================
-- MJ THE MUSICAL
-- ============================================================
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Myles Frost was discovered when his mother uploaded a YouTube video of him performing at a high school talent show in Rockville, Maryland, and the show''s producers spotted it online', 'cast', 'fact', 'He was a college audio engineering student when he was invited to audition'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Frost won the Tony for Best Leading Actor in a Musical at age 22, one of the youngest winners in the category', 'award', 'fact', 'His Broadway debut performance won the top acting prize'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Natasha Katz won the Tony for Best Lighting Design, using over 800 lighting fixtures to recreate the visual spectacle of a Michael Jackson concert', 'technical', 'fact', 'Katz used moving lights, follow spots, and strobe effects to simulate arena-scale production values on a Broadway stage'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Gareth Owen won the Tony for Best Sound Design, engineering the system to reproduce the impact of stadium-level bass response within the Neil Simon Theatre', 'technical', 'fact', 'The sound design makes the theater feel like a concert venue'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Peter Nigrini''s video and projection design uses LED screens and projection surfaces to recreate iconic music video sequences live on stage', 'technical', 'fact', 'The projections transform the stage into Thriller, Smooth Criminal, and other video worlds'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Christopher Wheeldon directed and choreographed the production, recreating Michael Jackson''s signature moves including the moonwalk, the anti-gravity lean, and the toe stand', 'production', 'fact', 'Wheeldon is primarily known as a ballet choreographer with the New York City Ballet'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The performers execute the anti-gravity lean using special shoes that lock into bolts embedded in the stage floor, the same patented mechanism Jackson invented for his live shows', 'backstage', 'fact', 'Patent US5255452A, originally filed by Jackson in 1992'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Lynn Nottage wrote the book, deliberately setting the story across two days in 1992 before the first allegations surfaced in 1993 to focus on Jackson''s artistry', 'production', 'fact', 'Nottage is the only woman to win the Pulitzer Prize for Drama twice'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show received 10 Tony nominations in 2022, the second-highest total that season', 'award', 'fact', 'Won 4 of its 10 nominations'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Derek McLane''s scenic design features a multilevel rehearsal studio set that transforms into concert stages, video shoots, and recording studios', 'design', 'fact', 'The flexible set allows rapid transitions between locations'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Paul Tazewell designed costumes that meticulously recreate Jackson''s iconic looks including the white glove, the red leather jacket, and the military-style tour outfits', 'design', 'fact', 'Each costume was researched against archival photos and video for accuracy'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The production has grossed over $319 million on Broadway with cumulative attendance of roughly 2.25 million', 'numbers', 'fact', 'Has repeatedly broken the Neil Simon Theatre''s house box office record'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'David Holcenberg and Jason Michael Webb won the Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Orchestrations, arranging Jackson''s catalog for a live Broadway pit band', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Translating pop and R&B recordings into live theatrical arrangements'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show was developed with a workshop at the Park Avenue Armory before moving to Broadway', 'history', 'fact', 'The Armory''s massive space allowed full-scale staging experiments'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Opened at the Neil Simon Theatre on February 1, 2022, after previews beginning December 6, 2021', 'production', 'fact', 'One of the first major new musicals to open after Broadway''s pandemic shutdown'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Smooth Criminal sequence features performers leaning at a 45-degree angle from the floor in unison, locked into the stage floor mechanism', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The entire ensemble performs the lean simultaneously in a feat of synchronized precision'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Rich and Tone Talauega, who worked as choreographers with the real Michael Jackson, served as associate choreographers alongside Wheeldon', 'production', 'fact', 'Their firsthand knowledge of Jackson''s movement vocabulary ensured authenticity'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The lead performer does approximately 25 full-out dance numbers per show, making it one of the most physically demanding roles on Broadway', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The role requires the athleticism of a professional dancer combined with acting and vocal ability'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Quick changes between iconic looks happen in as little as 30 seconds backstage with a team of dressers', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The costume changes are choreographed as precisely as the dance numbers'),
('MJ the Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Thriller sequence uses theatrical fog, UV-reactive costumes, and synchronized strobe lighting to recreate the zombie dance on stage', 'technical', 'fact', 'Transforms the theater into a horror movie set for the duration of the number'),

-- ============================================================
-- THE OUTSIDERS
-- ============================================================
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Won 4 Tony Awards in 2024 including Best Musical, Best Direction for Danya Taymor, Best Lighting Design, and Best Sound Design', 'award', 'fact', 'Taymor is only the 11th woman to win the Tony for Best Direction of a Musical'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Lighting designers Brian MacDevitt and Hana S. Kim won the Tony using a rig that shifts between golden sunset warmth and harsh sodium-vapor streetlight to evoke 1960s Tulsa', 'technical', 'fact', 'The lighting creates distinct emotional worlds for the Greasers and the Socs'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Sound designer Cody Spencer won the Tony for Best Sound Design, creating an immersive soundscape that places the audience inside the rumble', 'technical', 'fact', 'The sound design uses spatial audio to make scenes feel three-dimensional'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The set by AMP featuring Tatiana Kahvegian uses raw industrial scaffolding and metal platforms that the cast climbs, hangs from, and swings on during the show', 'design', 'fact', 'The set becomes a jungle gym, a bridge, a drive-in, and a church through actor interaction'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Rick and Jeff Kuperman choreographed the fight sequences as acrobatic, full-body physical theater rather than traditional stage combat', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The rumble sequence has performers flipping, rolling, and tumbling in coordinated chaos'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The first song written for the show was Stay Gold, and nearly nine years passed between writing that first number and the songs reaching Broadway', 'history', 'fact', 'A nearly decade-long development process'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The musical was originally set to premiere at the Goodman Theatre in Chicago in June 2020 but was canceled due to COVID, eventually premiering at La Jolla Playhouse in February 2023', 'history', 'fact', 'The pandemic delayed the show by nearly three years'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Angelina Jolie signed on as lead producer after her daughter brought her to see the show at La Jolla Playhouse', 'production', 'fact', 'Jolie and Debra Martin Chase accepted the Tony for Best Musical'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show received 12 Tony nominations in 2024, including two nominations in Best Featured Actor for Joshua Boone and Sky Lakota-Lynch', 'award', 'fact', 'Two actors from the same show competing in the same category'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Opened April 11, 2024, at the Bernard B. Jacobs Theatre after beginning previews March 16', 'production', 'fact', 'Extended from La Jolla due to high ticket demand before the Broadway transfer'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Music and lyrics by Jamestown Revival (Jonathan Clay and Zach Chance) and Justin Levine, blending Americana folk-rock with theatrical storytelling', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Jamestown Revival is an indie folk duo making their Broadway debut'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Book by Adam Rapp with Justin Levine, adapting S.E. Hinton''s 1967 novel which she wrote when she was 15 years old', 'production', 'fact', 'The novel was written by a teenager about teenagers'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Brody Grant originated the role of Ponyboy Curtis, performing the physically demanding role eight shows a week', 'cast', 'fact', 'Grant was nominated for the Tony for Best Leading Actor'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Original Broadway Cast Recording was nominated for a Grammy for Best Musical Theatre Album at the 67th Annual Grammy Awards', 'award', 'fact', 'Recognition for the show''s folk-rock score'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Director Danya Taymor staged the drive-in movie scene with the cast backlit against a massive projected screen, creating silhouettes that reference the 1983 Francis Ford Coppola film', 'technical', 'fact', 'A visual homage that connects the musical to its cinematic predecessor'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The ensemble performs a physical warm-up before every show that resembles a gymnastic training session more than a typical Broadway half-hour', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The show''s athletic demands require performers to be in peak physical condition'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The fire sequence uses theatrical haze, LED flame effects, and amber lighting to create the illusion of a burning church without real fire on stage', 'technical', 'fact', 'A technically complex effect that must look convincing while being completely safe'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The production uses period-accurate 1960s costumes including leather jackets, cuffed jeans, and white t-shirts for the Greasers, contrasted with preppy button-downs for the Socs', 'design', 'fact', 'The costume design instantly communicates class division'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The curtain call features the full cast performing a high-energy choreographic sequence set to the show''s rock arrangements', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The bow itself is a performance piece that sends the audience out on an adrenaline high'),
('The Outsiders', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'S.E. Hinton herself attended performances and gave the production her personal blessing', 'culture', 'fact', 'The author''s endorsement carried significant weight with fans of the novel'),

-- ============================================================
-- AVENUE Q
-- ============================================================
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'All four principal puppeteers — John Tartaglia, Stephanie D''Abruzzo, Rick Lyon, and Jennifer Barnhart — had worked as real Sesame Street performers before the show', 'cast', 'fact', 'The parody was performed by people who knew the real thing intimately'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'John Tartaglia served as Elmo''s understudy on Sesame Street at age 16, one of the youngest puppeteers ever on the show', 'cast', 'fact', 'He went from performing Elmo to parodying the entire Sesame format on Broadway'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Each puppet costs approximately $10,000 and requires about 120 hours of hand fabrication by designer Rick Lyon', 'design', 'fact', 'Lyon both designed the puppets and performed as Nicky and Trekkie Monster'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The puppeteers are completely visible to the audience throughout the show, operating the puppets in plain sight while simultaneously singing and acting', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The visible manipulation was a deliberate artistic choice that the audience accepts within minutes'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Beat Wicked for the Tony for Best Musical in 2003, one of the biggest upsets in Tony history', 'award', 'fact', 'The small-budget downtown show defeating the blockbuster was considered a shock'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Won 3 Tony Awards: Best Musical, Best Book for Jeff Whitty, and Best Original Score for Robert Lopez and Jeff Marx', 'award', 'fact', 'Robert Lopez later became the youngest EGOT winner in history'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Originally opened off-Broadway at the Vineyard Theatre in March 2003 before transferring to the Golden Theatre on Broadway in July 2003', 'production', 'fact', 'The off-Broadway success drove an unusually fast Broadway transfer'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The set was designed as a split-level apartment building facade, small enough to fit on the Golden Theatre''s intimate stage, one of the smallest houses on Broadway', 'design', 'fact', 'The modest scale was integral to the show''s scrappy, downtown charm'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Ran for 2,534 performances on Broadway before moving off-Broadway to New World Stages in 2009, where it continued running for years', 'numbers', 'fact', 'One of the few shows to successfully transfer from Broadway to off-Broadway'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Robert Lopez co-wrote the songs and went on to co-write the music for The Book of Mormon and Frozen, becoming the youngest person to achieve EGOT status', 'production', 'fact', 'Avenue Q launched one of the most successful songwriting careers in modern entertainment'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The production announced a national tour shortly before the Tony vote, which some speculated influenced voters; days later the tour was revealed to not exist', 'culture', 'fact', 'The phantom tour announcement became Broadway industry lore'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The puppet called Lucy the Slut requires two operators: one for the head and right hand, another for the left hand, coordinating in real time', 'backstage', 'fact', 'More complex puppets require a second performer working in close coordination'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'A small onstage band of 5 musicians accompanies the show, with keyboards, guitars, bass, and drums visible to the audience', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The intimate band size matches the show''s low-budget, downtown aesthetic'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Internet Is for Porn number became one of the first Broadway songs to go viral online, which was ironic given its subject matter about internet culture', 'culture', 'fact', 'The song''s viral spread predated YouTube and happened mostly through file sharing'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jeff Whitty''s book was the first Broadway musical script to include explicit puppet-on-puppet sexual content, which the creative team fought to keep past producers'' objections', 'history', 'fact', 'The scene became one of the show''s most talked-about moments'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Each puppet has a rod mechanism controlling one hand and the puppeteer''s own hand inside the other puppet hand, allowing remarkably expressive gesture work', 'design', 'fact', 'The rod-and-hand technique gives the puppets lifelike manual dexterity'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Stephanie D''Abruzzo was nominated for the Tony for Best Leading Actress for playing both Kate Monster and Lucy, performing two characters with distinct voices and puppet physicalities', 'cast', 'fact', 'Nominated for a leading role while operating puppets the entire time'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show was capitalized at approximately $3.5 million, a fraction of the cost of most Broadway musicals even in 2003', 'numbers', 'fact', 'Its low budget made it profitable relatively quickly'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Director Jason Moore staged the show to embrace the crudeness of both the humor and the puppet aesthetic, avoiding any attempt to hide the theatrical machinery', 'production', 'fact', 'Moore later directed the film Pitch Perfect'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Opened on Broadway on July 31, 2003, at the John Golden Theatre', 'production', 'fact', 'One of the smallest Broadway houses, with 805 seats'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show''s original development included workshops at the Eugene O''Neill Theater Center in Waterford, Connecticut', 'history', 'fact', 'The O''Neill Center has incubated dozens of shows that later reached Broadway'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Backup puppets for every character are maintained backstage in case of damage during performances', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The physical demands of eight shows a week cause wear and tear on the puppets'),
('Avenue Q', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Bad Idea Bears, a pair of cute-looking puppet bears that give terrible advice, are operated by actors who also play human roles in the show', 'cast', 'fact', 'Performers toggle between puppet operation and live acting within the same show'),

-- ============================================================
-- GUYS AND DOLLS
-- ============================================================
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jo Mielziner designed both the sets and the lighting for the original 1950 production, a dual role that is virtually unheard of today', 'design', 'fact', 'Mielziner is considered one of the greatest designers in Broadway history'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Michael Kidd choreographed the original and called it the best-integrated musical he ever worked on', 'production', 'fact', 'Kidd''s crap game ballet is one of the most celebrated dance sequences in Broadway history'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production opened November 24, 1950, at the 46th Street Theatre and ran for 1,200 performances', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A massive run for the early 1950s'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Won 5 Tony Awards in 1951 including Best Musical, Best Actor for Robert Alda, and Best Featured Actress for Isabel Bigley', 'award', 'fact', 'Robert Alda is the father of Alan Alda'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Frank Loesser wrote both the music and lyrics, crafting songs that range from operatic (My Time of Day) to comic patter (Adelaide''s Lament) to romantic ballad (I''ve Never Been in Love Before)', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The score''s versatility is considered one of the greatest achievements in Broadway songwriting'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Abe Burrows wrote the book but was denied program credit during the original run because he was blacklisted during the McCarthy era', 'history', 'fact', 'His name was eventually restored after he cooperated with the House Un-American Activities Committee'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'George S. Kaufman directed the original production, his last major Broadway hit, staging the Havana nightclub scene as an extended dance sequence', 'production', 'fact', 'Kaufman was better known as a playwright but brought sharp comedic timing to the direction'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Mielziner''s sets used painted drops and a revolving stage to transition between Times Square, the sewer, the Hot Box nightclub, and Havana without blackouts', 'design', 'fact', 'The seamless scenic flow kept the pace brisk and cinematic'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 1992 revival directed by Jerry Zaks starred Nathan Lane as Nathan Detroit, Peter Gallagher as Sky Masterson, and Faith Prince as Adelaide', 'cast', 'fact', 'Prince won the Tony for Best Leading Actress for her Adelaide'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 1992 revival ran for 1,143 performances at the Martin Beck Theatre, nearly matching the original production''s run', 'numbers', 'fact', 'One of the most successful Broadway revivals of the 1990s'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 1992 revival won 4 Tony Awards including Best Revival, and was choreographed by Christopher Chadman', 'award', 'fact', 'Tony Walton designed the sets, winning the Tony for Best Scenic Design'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Luck Be a Lady dice game sequence requires the entire male ensemble to perform synchronized choreography while crouching in a sewer set', 'backstage', 'fact', 'One of the most physically demanding ensemble numbers in the classic Broadway canon'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Based on the short stories of Damon Runyon, the show preserves Runyon''s distinctive present-tense, slang-heavy prose style in its dialogue', 'history', 'fact', 'The Runyonesque language is as much a character as any person in the show'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Hot Box Girls'' costumes include quick-change elements that allow the ensemble to shift from street clothes to nightclub outfits in under a minute', 'design', 'fact', 'The backstage dressing choreography is as precise as the onstage choreography'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Often called the perfect musical by critics, with Frank Rich of the New York Times calling it the greatest American musical ever written', 'culture', 'fact', 'A distinction shared by few other shows in the canon'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original orchestration by George Bassman and Ted Royal used a full Broadway pit orchestra with prominent brass to evoke the brassy energy of midcentury Times Square', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The big-band orchestration gives the score its swinging, urban personality'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Vivian Blaine originated the role of Miss Adelaide on Broadway and reprised the role in the 1955 film, one of few original cast members to transfer to the movie', 'cast', 'fact', 'Her adenoidal voice for the character became the definitive interpretation'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production''s poster by Al Hirschfeld became one of the most iconic theatrical images of the 20th century', 'culture', 'fact', 'Hirschfeld''s caricature style perfectly matched the show''s Runyon-esque world'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Sit Down, You''re Rockin'' the Boat number uses the full ensemble as a church congregation, building from a quiet hymn to a full gospel revival', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The escalation from stillness to pandemonium is one of Broadway''s great act-two showstoppers'),
('Guys and Dolls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Adelaide''s Lament, in which a character self-diagnoses psychosomatic illness from her fiance''s failure to commit, uses medical terminology delivered as a comic aria', 'song', 'fact', 'Loesser turned a medical textbook into one of Broadway''s funniest songs'),

-- ============================================================
-- COMPANY
-- ============================================================
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Boris Aronson''s original 1970 set featured a chrome-and-glass skeletal apartment structure with a working elevator that rose and descended during scenes', 'design', 'fact', 'The abstract set represented modern urban isolation through transparent architecture'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Dean Jones originated the role of Bobby in 1970 but left the show shortly after opening night, reportedly because the material about marriage failure too closely mirrored his own divorce', 'cast', 'fact', 'Larry Kert replaced him and played the role for the remainder of the run'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2006 revival directed by John Doyle had zero pit musicians — all 14 actors played instruments on stage throughout the entire show', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Raul Esparza played Bobby while also performing percussion and piano'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'In the 2006 Doyle production, Barbara Walsh played Joanne while simultaneously playing orchestra bells, and every cast member doubled on at least one instrument', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The actor-musician concept stripped the show to its emotional core'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Raul Esparza earned a Tony nomination for Best Leading Actor in the 2006 revival, performing complex Sondheim vocals while physically playing instruments', 'cast', 'fact', 'He performed Being Alive while moving between percussion and piano'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2021 gender-swapped revival by Marianne Elliott changed the protagonist from Bobby to Bobbie, a single woman, and adjusted the couples'' genders accordingly', 'production', 'fact', 'The first major gender-reconceived Sondheim revival on Broadway'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2021 revival played 9 preview performances in March 2020 before COVID shut Broadway for 20 months, then had to restart previews from scratch', 'production', 'fact', 'The cast held the show together through the longest Broadway shutdown in history'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Patti LuPone won the Tony for Best Featured Actress as Joanne in the 2021 revival at age 73, delivering the definitive Ladies Who Lunch of the modern era', 'award', 'fact', 'Her third Tony win across five decades of Broadway performance'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original 1970 production was directed by Harold Prince and conceived as a concept musical with no linear plot, a radical structure at the time', 'production', 'fact', 'Sondheim and Prince essentially invented the concept musical with this show'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jonathan Tunick''s original orchestrations use a 16-piece orchestra with prominent brass, woodwinds, and percussion reflecting the urban energy of 1970s Manhattan', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Tunick has orchestrated virtually every Sondheim musical since Company'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production ran for 705 performances at the Alvin Theatre, beginning April 26, 1970', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A strong run for an unconventional show with no traditional love story'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Won 6 Tony Awards in 1971 including Best Musical, Best Score, Best Lyrics, and Best Book', 'award', 'fact', 'Sondheim won both the music and lyrics Tonys, a dual achievement'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Michael Bennett choreographed the original production, using dance as an expression of urban anxiety and social performance', 'production', 'fact', 'Bennett went on to create A Chorus Line five years later'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'George Furth wrote the book based on a collection of one-act plays about marriage that he originally intended as a straight play', 'history', 'fact', 'Sondheim suggested turning the individual plays into a single musical about a bachelor observing married life'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The iconic original cast recording was produced by Thomas Z. Shepard and is considered one of the finest Broadway recordings ever made', 'culture', 'fact', 'The recording captured performances by Elaine Stritch, Dean Jones, and the full original company'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Elaine Stritch nearly didn''t make it through recording The Ladies Who Lunch for the cast album, requiring over 20 takes due to exhaustion and nerves', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The struggle was documented and became theatrical legend'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Bunny Christie designed the 2021 revival set as a giant box that opened and reconfigured like a dollhouse, with rooms appearing and disappearing', 'design', 'fact', 'The modular set reflected Bobbie''s shifting perspective on domestic life'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Being Alive finale was originally written as a more cynical number called Happily Ever After, which Sondheim replaced at Dean Jones''s request for something more hopeful', 'song', 'fact', 'The song''s evolution from cynicism to yearning transformed the show''s ending'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Matt Doyle won the Tony for Best Featured Actor in the 2021 revival playing Jamie, a role gender-swapped from a female character in the original', 'award', 'fact', 'Not Getting Married Today became a male comedic showcase in the revival'),
('Company', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Katrina Lenk originated the role of Bobbie in the 2021 revival, having won the Tony for Best Leading Actress in The Band''s Visit just two years earlier', 'cast', 'fact', 'Two Tony-caliber leading roles in consecutive Sondheim-adjacent productions'),

-- ============================================================
-- DREAMGIRLS
-- ============================================================
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Lighting designer Tharon Musser used approximately 650 lighting instruments with around 240 programmed cues on a computerized memory board, one of the highest cue counts on Broadway at that time', 'technical', 'fact', 'Musser pioneered computerized lighting on Broadway with A Chorus Line and pushed it further here'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Robin Wagner''s set consisted of five aluminum light bridge towers on tracks that moved across the stage in various configurations, weighing approximately 5,000 pounds total', 'design', 'fact', 'The towers created every location — recording studios, nightclubs, concert stages — through light and movement alone'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Michael Bennett directed and choreographed the original, staging it so that no applause break followed And I Am Telling You I''m Not Going to heighten the dramatic impact', 'backstage', 'fact', 'Bennett deliberately killed the expected showstopper moment to serve the story'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'On opening night, the audience broke Bennett''s no-applause staging and stopped the show cold after Jennifer Holliday''s performance of And I Am Telling You', 'culture', 'fact', 'The ovation reportedly lasted several minutes and became Broadway legend'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jennifer Holliday was 20 years old when she originated the role of Effie White, delivering a performance so physically intense she lost her voice multiple times during the run', 'cast', 'fact', 'Her raw emotional power in the role has never been replicated on stage'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Won 6 Tony Awards in 1982 including Best Actress for Holliday, Best Actor for Ben Harney, Best Book, Best Lighting, Best Choreography, and Best Featured Actor for Cleavant Derricks', 'award', 'fact', 'Did not win Best Musical, losing to Nine in an upset'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The production used no traditional scenery or backdrop — the entire visual world was created by the moving towers, projected images, and Musser''s lighting', 'design', 'fact', 'Wagner and Musser created one of Broadway''s most minimalist yet spectacular designs'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Henry Krieger composed the music and Tom Eyen wrote the book and lyrics, creating a score that spans 20 years of popular music from R&B to disco to pop', 'production', 'fact', 'The score is a history of Black popular music told through a fictional group'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production opened December 20, 1981, at the Imperial Theatre and ran for 1,521 performances', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A strong four-year run for a show that lost Best Musical'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The five towers could move independently on stage-spanning tracks, creating proscenium-like frames, corridor effects, or spreading apart to reveal full-stage concert scenes', 'technical', 'fact', 'The automation tracks were built into the stage floor specifically for this production'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Bennett staged the show as a continuous cinematic flow with no blackouts between scenes, using the moving towers to dissolve from one location to the next', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The seamless transitions were revolutionary and influenced decades of Broadway staging'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The costume design by Theoni V. Aldredge tracked the evolution of fashion from the early 1960s through the early 1980s, with each time period reflected in the performers'' wardrobe', 'design', 'fact', 'Aldredge used costumes as a timeline, making the passage of years visible at a glance'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Holliday''s cast recording of And I Am Telling You won the Grammy for Best Female R&B Vocal Performance, crossing over from Broadway to mainstream pop recognition', 'award', 'fact', 'One of the rare instances of a Broadway performance winning a pop Grammy'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original orchestra included a full R&B rhythm section with electric bass, drums, guitars, and keyboards alongside traditional Broadway pit instruments', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Harold Wheeler''s orchestrations gave the show authentic R&B and Motown energy'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Bennett''s staging had the Dreams performing facing upstage during their early career scenes, then gradually turning to face the audience as they became famous', 'backstage', 'fact', 'A subtle directorial choice that physically mapped the group''s rise to stardom'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Cleavant Derricks won the Tony for Best Featured Actor as James Thunder Early, playing an aging R&B star whose decline mirrors the Dreams'' rise', 'award', 'fact', 'His performance anchored the show''s most tragic subplot'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show''s story was widely understood as a fictionalized version of The Supremes and Motown Records, though the creators always denied a direct correlation', 'history', 'fact', 'Diana Ross reportedly was not pleased with the parallels'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Michael Peters co-choreographed with Bennett, bringing authentic R&B and soul dance vocabulary to the production', 'production', 'fact', 'Peters also choreographed Michael Jackson''s Thriller and Beat It music videos'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The One Night Only number required the full company to perform a concert staging complete with working handheld microphones, monitor wedges, and concert lighting', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The scene recreated a live concert experience on the Broadway stage'),
('Dreamgirls', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Sheryl Lee Ralph originated the role of Deena Jones and was nominated for the Tony for Best Actress, 40 years before winning an Emmy for Abbott Elementary', 'cast', 'fact', 'Her Broadway career preceded her late-career television breakthrough by four decades'),

-- ============================================================
-- THE MUSIC MAN
-- ============================================================
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2022 revival grossed over $163 million on Broadway, shattering the Winter Garden Theatre''s box-office record 48 times', 'numbers', 'fact', 'Hugh Jackman''s star power drove historically high grosses'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2022 revival orchestra has 24 musicians, unusually large for modern Broadway where most shows use 15-20', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The full-sized orchestra honors Meredith Willson''s lush original orchestrations'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Robert Preston had never sung publicly before being cast in the original 1957 production, and Meredith Willson wrote the rapid-fire patter songs specifically to work with his limited vocal range', 'cast', 'fact', 'Willson turned a non-singer into Broadway''s most convincing con man'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Meredith Willson rewrote the show over 30 times across six years of development before it reached Broadway in 1957', 'history', 'fact', 'An extraordinarily long gestation for a musical that feels effortlessly crafted'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original 1957 production won 5 Tony Awards including Best Musical, beating West Side Story in one of the most debated Tony races in history', 'award', 'fact', 'Two of the greatest musicals ever written competed in the same year'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production ran for 1,375 performances at the Majestic Theatre, beginning December 19, 1957', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A hit run that established the show as a Broadway classic'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Willson based the show on his own childhood in Mason City, Iowa, and the character of Marian the Librarian was inspired by a real Mason City librarian', 'history', 'fact', 'The autobiographical roots give the show its authentic small-town detail'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2022 revival starred Hugh Jackman and Sutton Foster, reuniting two of Broadway''s biggest stars, and opened February 10, 2022, at the Winter Garden Theatre', 'production', 'fact', 'The most anticipated Broadway revival in years'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Santo Loquasto designed the 2022 revival''s sets and costumes, creating a painterly Americana vision of River City with hand-painted drops and period-accurate wardrobe', 'design', 'fact', 'Loquasto is a frequent Woody Allen collaborator bringing his cinematic eye to Broadway'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Seventy-Six Trombones number in the 2022 revival features an actual marching band of child performers crossing the stage', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The children rehearse separately and integrate with the adult cast for the big numbers'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Warren Carlyle choreographed the 2022 revival, staging the Shipoopi number as a full-company athletic dance sequence in a gymnasium', 'production', 'fact', 'Carlyle won the Tony nomination for his energetic, period-appropriate choreography'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Ya Got Trouble number is performed almost entirely as rhythmic speech without traditional melody, requiring the actor to sustain energy for over four minutes of rapid-fire patter', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The song is essentially a sales pitch performed as a one-man show'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Willson used a barbershop quartet — the Buffalo Bills — integrated into the original Broadway cast, performing four-part harmony arrangements that he wrote specifically for their voices', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The quartet won the Tony along with the show''s other musical achievements'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Wells Fargo Wagon number requires the entire company including children to perform coordinated choreography while singing in harmony, building from anticipation to full celebration', 'backstage', 'fact', 'One of the most complex full-company numbers in the classic musical theater canon'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2022 revival ran for 383 performances before closing January 1, 2023, a relatively short run driven by Jackman''s limited availability', 'numbers', 'fact', 'Despite high grosses, the run was always intended to be finite'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Oren Jacoby directed a 2003 TV movie version starring Matthew Broderick, but the original 1962 film with Robert Preston remains the definitive screen version', 'culture', 'fact', 'Preston is the rare Broadway originator who also starred in the film adaptation'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2022 production was capitalized at approximately $20 million, one of the most expensive revival productions in Broadway history', 'numbers', 'fact', 'The investment was considered justified by Jackman''s proven box-office appeal'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Willson composed the score using distinctly American musical idioms: marching band, barbershop quartet, soft-shoe, and Midwestern hymn singing', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'No other Broadway score so completely embodies small-town American musical traditions'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The think system — Harold Hill''s claim that children can learn to play instruments just by thinking about the music — was Willson''s satirical take on positive thinking movements of the 1950s', 'history', 'fact', 'The con is both the show''s central joke and its most heartfelt message'),
('The Music Man', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Onna White choreographed the original 1957 production, winning acclaim for dance sequences that incorporated everyday small-town movement into theatrical choreography', 'production', 'fact', 'White''s choreography made ordinary townspeople move like a Broadway ensemble'),

-- ============================================================
-- BACK TO THE FUTURE: THE MUSICAL
-- ============================================================
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The DeLorean time machine appears to fly off the stage using a combination of LED effects, projection, theatrical fog, and a practical car body mounted on a hydraulic lift system', 'technical', 'fact', 'The time travel moment is the show''s signature technical achievement'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The clock tower finale uses over 300 individual lighting cues in a sequence lasting approximately 5 minutes, simulating the lightning strike that sends Marty back to 1985', 'technical', 'fact', 'One of the most cue-dense sequences on Broadway'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Tim Hatley designed the set which features a full-sized DeLorean replica that transforms from a stationary car into the time travel vehicle through automated scenic elements', 'design', 'fact', 'The car is the most complex practical prop on a Broadway stage'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Opened at the Winter Garden Theatre in New York on July 25, 2023, after a successful West End run at the Adelphi Theatre in London beginning in 2021', 'production', 'fact', 'One of the few recent musicals to transfer from London to Broadway rather than the reverse'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Original songs by Alan Silvestri and Glen Ballard expand the film''s musical landscape while the score incorporates iconic moments from Silvestri''s original film score', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Silvestri composed both the original 1985 film score and the new stage songs'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The production uses Finn Ross''s video and projection design to create the time travel vortex, the speedometer counting to 88 mph, and the lightning effects', 'technical', 'fact', 'Projection replaces what would be impossible to stage with practical scenery alone'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Director John Rando staged the skateboard chase sequence using a combination of choreography, rolling platforms, and projection to simulate Marty''s escape on a skateboard', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The sequence was one of the most challenging staging problems in the show'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The Enchantment Under the Sea dance sequence recreates the 1955 prom with period-accurate costumes, a live onstage band, and choreography by Chris Bailey', 'design', 'fact', 'The prom scene shifts from period romance to rock and roll in a single number'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Bob Gale, who co-wrote the original screenplay with Robert Zemeckis, wrote the book for the stage musical', 'production', 'fact', 'The film''s co-creator adapted his own work for the stage'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Casey Nicholaw was originally attached to direct and choreograph before John Rando took over the production', 'history', 'fact', 'A significant creative team change during development'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show requires extensive pyrotechnic effects including flash pots and spark effects for the lightning strike and the DeLorean''s time travel activation', 'technical', 'fact', 'A licensed pyrotechnics operator works every performance'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Hugh Coles originated the role of Marty McFly on Broadway, following Roger Bart who originated Doc Brown in both London and New York', 'cast', 'fact', 'Bart brought continuity from the West End production to Broadway'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Tim Hatley''s scenic design transforms the stage from 1985 Hill Valley to 1955 Hill Valley using tracked wagons, flying scenery, and reversible set pieces', 'design', 'fact', 'The two time periods share the same basic geography but with different visual details'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 88 mph speedometer effect uses a practical LED display built into the DeLorean prop that counts up in real time as the car appears to accelerate', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The audience watches the numbers climb in the crucial countdown moments'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The London production won the Olivier Award for Best New Musical in 2022', 'award', 'fact', 'The West End success built momentum for the Broadway transfer'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Sound designer Gareth Owen created an immersive soundscape that includes the iconic DeLorean engine sounds and the Huey Lewis songs woven into the theatrical audio mix', 'technical', 'fact', 'Owen bridges the film''s famous sound world with live theatrical audio'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Nick Lidster designed the costumes, meticulously recreating Marty''s iconic red puffer vest, jeans, and Nike sneakers alongside Doc Brown''s lab coat and wild hair', 'design', 'fact', 'The film''s costumes are so iconic that any deviation would be noticed by audiences'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Power of Love and Johnny B. Goode are performed live on stage, integrating the licensed songs from the film into the theatrical score', 'song', 'fact', 'The familiar songs serve as bridge moments between the film audience''s memory and the stage experience'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The automation system moves the DeLorean on and off stage using a tracked platform embedded in the stage floor, requiring precise timing with lighting and sound cues', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The car''s entrances and exits are choreographed like a character''s blocking'),
('Back to the Future: The Musical', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show''s development spanned over a decade, with Zemeckis and Gale first exploring a stage adaptation in the early 2010s', 'history', 'fact', 'The film''s creators waited until they felt the technology existed to do it justice on stage'),

-- ============================================================
-- & JULIET
-- ============================================================
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The score uses existing pop songs written by Max Martin, the Swedish songwriter responsible for hits by Britney Spears, NSYNC, the Backstreet Boys, Katy Perry, and The Weeknd', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'Martin has written more number-one hits than any songwriter since the Beatles'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Sound designer Gareth Owen designed a concert-level audio system with over 100 speakers to deliver the pop score at arena volume within the Stephen Sondheim Theatre', 'technical', 'fact', 'The sound pressure level is closer to a pop concert than a typical Broadway musical'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Paloma Young designed over 100 costumes blending Elizabethan silhouettes with contemporary pop-star fashion, using neon colors and metallic fabrics', 'design', 'fact', 'Period ruffs and corsets are remixed with platform boots and sequins'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Opened on Broadway at the Stephen Sondheim Theatre on November 17, 2022, after transferring from a hit West End run at the Shaftesbury Theatre in London', 'production', 'fact', 'The London production opened in November 2019 just months before the pandemic'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show was conceived by David West Read, a writer on Schitt''s Creek, who imagined what would happen if Shakespeare''s wife Anne Hathaway rewrote the ending of Romeo and Juliet', 'history', 'fact', 'Read brought his TV comedy sensibility to the Broadway book'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Received 9 Tony nominations in 2023 including Best Musical, though it did not win the top prize', 'award', 'fact', 'Lost Best Musical to Kimberly Akimbo'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Lorna Courtney originated the role of Juliet on Broadway, making her Broadway debut in the lead role', 'cast', 'fact', 'Courtney''s powerhouse vocals anchor the pop score nightly'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Betsy Wolfe plays Anne Hathaway (Shakespeare''s wife, not the actress), who becomes the show''s driving force by rewriting the story', 'cast', 'fact', 'The meta-theatrical conceit puts the female perspective in control of the narrative'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The jukebox score includes rearrangements of Baby One More Time, Larger Than Life, Roar, I Want It That Way, and Can''t Stop the Feeling among dozens of Martin-penned hits', 'song', 'fact', 'Bill Sherman arranged the pop songs for a live Broadway orchestra'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Soutra Gilmour designed the set as a candy-colored pop-art version of Shakespeare''s Globe Theatre, with neon signage and oversized scenic elements', 'design', 'fact', 'The design is deliberately anachronistic, matching the show''s mashup of Elizabethan and modern'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Director Luke Sheppard staged the show with concert-style choreography by Jennifer Weber, blending hip-hop, voguing, and commercial dance', 'production', 'fact', 'Weber''s choreography gives the show its contemporary pop-concert energy'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Howard Hudson''s lighting design uses over 500 moving lights and LED fixtures to create a concert atmosphere that shifts color and intensity with each pop song', 'technical', 'fact', 'The lighting rig is sized more like a touring pop concert than a Broadway show'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Justin David Sullivan plays the nonbinary character May, one of the first prominently featured nonbinary characters in a Broadway musical', 'cast', 'fact', 'The character''s identity is central to the plot and celebrated rather than tokenized'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Max Martin reportedly attended Broadway performances and was moved to tears seeing his songs recontextualized in a theatrical narrative', 'culture', 'fact', 'The pop hitmaker had never been involved in a theatrical production before'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show features extensive use of confetti cannons, streamers, and audience interaction during the finale, blurring the line between Broadway show and pop concert', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The celebratory ending sends audiences out in a party atmosphere'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Paulo Szot plays Lance, a role created for the Broadway production that was not in the original London cast', 'cast', 'fact', 'The Broadway transfer added and expanded roles from the West End version'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The production has grossed consistently over $1 million per week on Broadway, proving strong commercial viability', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A reliable earner in its second year on Broadway'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Quick changes between Elizabethan and modern costumes happen in under 45 seconds with teams of dressers stationed at multiple backstage positions', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The costume transitions mirror the show''s constant shifting between time periods'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Stark Sands plays William Shakespeare as a comedic figure whose ego is repeatedly punctured by his wife''s superior storytelling instincts', 'cast', 'fact', 'Shakespeare is played for laughs rather than reverence'),
('& Juliet', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The show includes a live onstage band visible behind a scrim, performing the pop arrangements in real time rather than using tracks', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The visible band reinforces the concert-show hybrid format'),

-- ============================================================
-- FUNNY GIRL
-- ============================================================
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original 1964 production went through 8 directors during development before Garson Kanin was credited, though Jerome Robbins was brought in to restage large portions before opening', 'production', 'fact', 'One of the most troubled development processes in Broadway history'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Barbra Streisand was 21 years old when she originated the role of Fanny Brice, catapulting from a nightclub singer to the biggest star on Broadway overnight', 'cast', 'fact', 'The show made her a household name virtually overnight'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production ran for 1,348 performances at the Winter Garden Theatre, beginning March 26, 1964', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A massive hit driven almost entirely by Streisand''s star power'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jule Styne composed the music and Bob Merrill wrote the lyrics, with the song People becoming one of the best-selling singles from a Broadway show in the 1960s', 'song', 'fact', 'People reached number 5 on the Billboard Hot 100'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2022 revival initially starred Beanie Feldstein, who departed early and was replaced by Lea Michele in a casting change that generated massive media attention', 'cast', 'fact', 'Michele''s casting became one of the most-discussed Broadway stories of the decade'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'After Lea Michele joined the 2022 revival, the show''s weekly gross jumped by approximately $1 million, with the production becoming one of the hottest tickets on Broadway', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A rare instance of a cast replacement dramatically changing a show''s commercial fortunes'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2022 revival at the August Wilson Theatre was the first Broadway revival of the show in its nearly 60-year history', 'production', 'fact', 'The original production''s close association with Streisand had made it untouchable for decades'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Don''t Rain on My Parade closes the first act with a sequence that originally required Streisand to stride downstage on a moving treadmill while the set flew away behind her', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The staging creates the illusion of Fanny moving forward while the world recedes'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Robert Randolph designed the original sets using a series of painted drops and rolling platforms that evoked the Ziegfeld Follies era', 'design', 'fact', 'The design shifted between intimate domestic scenes and lavish Follies production numbers'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Michael Mayer directed the 2022 revival with choreography by Ellenore Scott, updating the staging for a modern audience while preserving the iconic musical numbers', 'production', 'fact', 'Mayer previously directed Spring Awakening and Hedwig and the Angry Inch'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2022 revival orchestra maintained a full Broadway pit with traditional big-band orchestrations honoring the 1960s sound of the original', 'orchestra', 'fact', 'The lush orchestrations are essential to the show''s period atmosphere'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'David Zinn designed the 2022 revival sets, creating a more cinematic staging with projections and video elements not available in the 1964 original', 'design', 'fact', 'Modern technology allowed scenic transitions the original couldn''t achieve'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Streisand''s performance was so dominant that the role was considered unplayable by another actress for decades, a stigma that hung over every casting discussion', 'culture', 'fact', 'The shadow of the original performance made the show uniquely difficult to revive'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The I''m the Greatest Star number requires the performer to demonstrate physical comedy, vocal power, and comedic timing in a 6-minute tour de force that introduces the character', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The number is essentially an audition within the show and sets the bar for the entire evening'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Isobel Lennart wrote the original book based on the real life of Fanny Brice, though significant liberties were taken with the timeline and relationships', 'history', 'fact', 'Harvey Fierstein revised the book for the 2022 revival'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The roller-skate scene in the Ziegfeld number requires the performer to skate on stage while singing and interacting with the ensemble in full Follies costume', 'backstage', 'fact', 'A technically demanding moment that combines athletic ability with vocal performance'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Ramin Karimloo played Nick Arnstein in the 2022 revival opposite both Feldstein and Michele', 'cast', 'fact', 'Karimloo provided continuity through the production''s tumultuous casting changes'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The original production was nominated for 8 Tony Awards but won zero, losing Best Musical to Hello, Dolly! in one of the most competitive Tony years ever', 'award', 'fact', 'One of the biggest Tony shutouts for a commercially successful show'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The My Man finale is performed as a simple spotlight solo with minimal staging, stripping away all production elements to leave the performer alone with the audience', 'backstage', 'fact', 'The stark contrast with the earlier production numbers makes the emotional impact devastating'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'Jane Lynch replaced Michele as Fanny''s mother Mrs. Brice during the 2022 revival run', 'cast', 'fact', 'Lynch brought her own comedic star power to the supporting role'),
('Funny Girl', 'Broadway Musical', 0, 'The 2022 revival ran for 695 performances at the August Wilson Theatre', 'numbers', 'fact', 'A solid commercial run boosted significantly by the Michele casting event'),
